<title>
Countershaft Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206015">Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206021">Countershaft Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5206022001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Supporting the gear on the concave side of the puller can cause damage to the gear.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to support the gear on the flat side of the puller.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove circlip (1) using special tool and then remove washer.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B031">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09900-06107">
09900–06107
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520049.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.533mm" ver = "01" gw = "79" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left bearing (2) and 6th gear (3) using bearing puller (4) and hydraulic press, and then remove 5th gear spacer.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Using an inappropriate hydraulic press or bearing puller could cause personal injury.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Make sure that both the hydraulic press and bearing puller are capable of safely bearing a load of at least 5 tons (11,000 lbs).
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520050.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "53.415mm" ver = "01" gw = "133" gh = "135"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.695in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Countershaft
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply bearing puller (3) to 4th gear (2) and remove 5th gear (1) with 4th gear using hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520060.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.118mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "128"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove circlip (1) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B032">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09900-06107">
09900–06107
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520051.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.896mm" ver = "01" gw = "119" gh = "150"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply bearing puller (3) to 2nd gear (2) and remove 3rd gear (1) with 2nd gear using hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0B520061.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.971mm" ver = "01" gw = "91" gh = "114"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply bearing puller (4) to reverse gear (3) and remove low speed synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly (1), 1st gear (2) with reverse gear using hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAY301520052.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.894mm" ver = "01" gw = "119" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Grind portion “a” of right bearing (1) using grinder (2) as shown.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The shaft (3) will be damaged if the bearing is ground too much.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit the amount of grinding to the minimum amount necessary.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520035.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.939mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Break the thinnest portion of bearing inner race (2) with a chisel (1) and remove bearing.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520036.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.523mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "107"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5206022002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206023">Countershaft Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206027">Gear Shift Shaft and Fork Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fit low speed synchronizer sleeve (1) to hub (2) and 3 keys (3) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
No specific direction is assigned to low speed synchronizer hub and each key but it is assigned as assembly.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<title>
